&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Semafor is a global news platform for an increasingly complex world in which consumers are overwhelmed by too many news sources and unsure what to trust. We are building Semafor to enable world-class journalists to deliver reporting and insights with rigor in journalistic forms that ensure a new level of transparency. Our editors and reporters distill the most important stories from all over in formats that uncover the forces shaping the stories, explain the interests behind polarizing narratives, and replenish the stock of shared facts. As a global platform, Semafor recognizes that smart people can disagree and that informed readers need to understand alternative points of view from competing centers of power and culture in a multi-polar world. Want to join us? Read on.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Semafor is seeking an experienced Audience Booker to support curated roundtables and private convenings on the sidelines of &lt;strong&gt;Semafor World Economy&lt;/strong&gt; in April.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not high-volume event marketing. This is high-judgment, executive-level curation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Audience Booker will lead guest strategy, targeting, and outreach for invitation-only roundtables designed for senior decision-makers. The role sits within the Audience team and works cross-functionally with editorial, revenue, and operations to ensure each convening is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategically composed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully subscribed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Senior in caliber&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balanced in perspective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operationally tight&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a contract role requiring discretion, speed, strong executive communication skills, and sharp editorial judgment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Audience Curation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own guest targeting and outreach strategy for private roundtables and executive convenings&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape attendee composition aligned with editorial framing and partner objectives&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curate rooms primarily composed of C-suite and senior executive leaders&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure thoughtful balance across sector, function, geography, and perspective&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain sensitivity to competitive dynamics and stakeholder considerations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exercise independent editorial judgment to protect the integrity and quality of the room&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Booking &amp;amp; Fill Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive event fill while preserving appropriate seniority and room quality&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor RSVP flow, declines, booking risk, and pipeline health&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively manage capacity, fill ratios, and composition “health”&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flag risk early and escalate where appropriate&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Outreach &amp;amp; Communications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and deploy polished, senior-level invitations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage confirmations, attendance visibility, and executive communications&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage directly with CEOs, senior leaders, and their offices&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct targeted research on prospective and confirmed attendees&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and outreach to communications leads

