&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;End-to-end project and account manage a selection of Semafor’s marquee events (e.g. Davos activations, signature accounts, the Semafor World Economy Annual Convening as well as custom client events, on-site at Semafor HQ in Washington, DC, as well as nationally and internationally, across venue logistics, catering, AV, decor, and on-site execution/staffing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead sponsor client relationships from sale through event delivery, ensuring best-in-class client service, engagement, and value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage event budgets, timelines, and project plans for a selection of Semafor’s marquee events&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide regular updates and reports to clients and internal stakeholders on event planning progress and budget management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with Semafor’s Senior Creative Director on overall event design Contract and manage vendors for AV, scenic, F&amp;amp;B and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage event staff and internal volunteers leading up to, and on the day of events, ensuring everyone understands their roles and responsibilities and executes them accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage event set-up, tear-down, and onsite execution to ensure events run smoothly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all health and safety regulations, and manage any necessary permits and insurance requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage key vendor relationships, deliverables, and timelines throughout the event planning process&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend new and emerging offsite venues for a variety of event types in Washington DC, New York, and other select cities as-required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide logistical and backend support on load in and event days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with and support other members of the events team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes you qualified&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor&#39;s degree is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in meeting/event planning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years in partner account management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong professional meeting planning skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working alongside clients to understand, capture and deliver a premium partner experience

